                            <layout>The texts run from folio A1 to A27, and from B1 to B26, B27 is left blank.
                                The beginning of a text is precedeed by the <foreign>bindu na godang</foreign><g type="B1"/> whereas the division into smaller sections of the texts is stresssed by the <foreign>bindu na metmet</foreign> <g type="B2"/>.
                                From from B1 to B9 the internal division of the text are stressed by another type of <foreign>bindu na metmet</foreign> in which its upper right-side has been elongated shaping a single black line <g type="BL"/>. The black line preceedes and runs parallel to the first line of the text, until the right-side margin.
                                On these same folios, the each small section of text is accompanied by a drawing, rapresenting different antrophomorphic figures.</layout>
